==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sanbenito
<hw>San`be*ni"to</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp. & Pg.
<ets>sambenito</ets>, contr. from L. <ets>saccus</ets> sack +
<ets>benedictus</ets> blessed.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Anciently, a
sackcloth coat worn by penitents on being reconciled to the
church.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A garnment or cap, or sometimes both, painted with
flames, figures, etc., and worn by persons who had been examined by the
Inquisition and were brought forth for punishment at the
auto-da-f⟦eacute⟧.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sancte bell</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Sance-bell</ent>⟦br⟧
